bin/

# Stray binaries from `go build ./cmd/<name>/` invoked from go/ without -o.
# Go names the output after the package's directory and drops it at go/<name>.
# Anchored with a leading slash so each entry matches go/<name> only, not the
# cmd/<name>/ subdir. Completeness is enforced by
# scripts/test-cmd-gitignore-parity.sh (precommit) — a new cmd/<name>/ without
# coverage here fails the gate, so this list can't silently drift (bug 736).
# Glob families (/*-audit-emit, /curate-*) cover whole cmd families in one line.
/audit-emit
/*-audit-emit
/action-docs-corpus-gen
/arcreview-snapshot-recover
/backfill-bug-864-gap-events
/chain-replay-verify
/codemap-gen
/corpos-gate
/commit-landed-emit
/curate-*
/event-registry
/grounding-events-processor
/parse-context-bench
/toolkit-proxy
/toolkit-server

# Go test binaries left by `go test -c ./<pkg>/`. The plain `go test ./...`
# invocation we use in CI / pre-commit doesn't produce these, but explicit -c
# runs do and the artifacts persist in the worktree. Ignore them so they don't
# clutter `git status` and risk an accidental `git add .`.
*.test

# go-mutesting (make mutest) writes its JSON report to the cwd (go/). It's an
# on-demand analysis artifact, never committed.
/report.json
